"I've really been looking forward to trying this collaboration between Sierra Nevada and Ballast Point. Served from a 12 oz. bottle this beer is a pale slightly amber gold. It has a decent head with good retention that leaves moderate lacing. Aroma is full-bodied with big orange and pine notes right up front.  Taste continues with bold hop and citrus presence as well as a nice alcohol wallop lurking in the background. Not especially surprising from an 8.5 % ABV brew categorized as an imperial pale lager. Mouthfeel is a little thinner than I expected, but still pretty decent with a level of carbonation that is not overwhelming. This is a potent brew with plenty of hops as I would expect from these two breweries, but definitely not to be classified as sessionable."
