"Aroma of green citric hops and a faint whiff of ethanol along with some muddled light caramel notes. Taste is smooth and similar in nature, bit of spritzy citrus up front, lightly 'oily' in the middle and finishing with a brief linger of hop spice. Firm in feel and lightly coarse in nature yet creamy at the same time given the hop balance. Warming brings forth more robust and resinous hop notes and a fuller less oily feel. Smoooth and easy. The initial waft of ethanol is now masked by the hop charge. I suspect we'll be seeing this one again. Nicely done."
