"12 ounce bottle into lager glass, bottled on 6/3/2014. Pours crystal clear deep gold color with a 1-2 finger dense and rocky off white head with great retention, that reduces to a nice cap that lingers. Spotty soapy lacing clings down the glass, with a moderate amount of streaming carbonation retaining the head. Aromas of grapefruit, mango, pineapple, lemon zest, orange peel, floral, grass, light pine, light caramel, bread, and floral/grassy earthiness. Very nice aromas with good complexity and balance of bright citrus/tropical hops and moderate malt sweetness; with good strength. Taste of big grapefruit, mango, pineapple, lemon zest, orange peel, floral, grass, light pine, light caramel, bread, and floral/grassy earthiness. Good amount of pine/grassy bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of grapefruit, pineapple, mango, lemon/orange zest, floral, grass, light pine, light caramel, bread, and floral/grassy earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Very nice complexity and balance of bright citrus/tropical hops and moderate malt sweetness; with a nice malt/bitterness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a smooth, crisp, and lightly creamy/sticky mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a very nice IPL style. All around good complexity and balance of bright citrus/tropical hops and moderate malt sweetness; and very smooth and crisp to drink. A very enjoyable offering."
