"Pours a nice medium amber-ish gold color. The liquid has excellent clarity. Fine bubbles in the head, which is pure white. There’s a little bit of lacing and the head has ok retention for a lager. The aroma is sweet with malt and hops. The malt is honey with light caramel. Rather sugary. Floral, pine and citrus hoppiness. Citrus is probably the strongest of the three. Mostly grapefruit. It smells like pine needles and grapefruit rind in honey with a dose of lager yeastiness. The taste is similarly on the sweet side. The beer dries out some in the finish, but it’s a bit too big for its own good, in my opinion. There’s a fair bit of malt character, more of that sweet honeyed grain flavor. Citrus and pine hop character with only moderate bitterness. Some booze. Very nice mouthfeel. Light on the palate for the abv. Fairly easy to drink. Almost crisp. Some hop oiliness. I just think the sweetness and booze creeps in a bit too much, particularly if you let it warm up at all."
